# Design Tokens - Tetris

This project uses a retro arcade design system defined in `.specs/design-system/tokens.md`.

## Token Reference

When implementing UI, use these token names rather than hardcoded values:

### Game Colors
- `color-void` - Deep black background (#0a0a0f)
- `color-grid-bg` - Game board background (#12121a)
- `color-grid-line` - Grid lines (#1e1e2e)
- `color-chrome` - UI panel backgrounds (#16161e)

### Tetromino Colors
- `color-piece-i` - I-piece cyan (#00f5ff)
- `color-piece-o` - O-piece yellow (#ffd700)
- `color-piece-t` - T-piece purple (#bf00ff)
- `color-piece-s` - S-piece green (#00ff66)
- `color-piece-z` - Z-piece red (#ff3366)
- `color-piece-j` - J-piece blue (#3366ff)
- `color-piece-l` - L-piece orange (#ff9933)

### UI Accents
- `color-accent-primary` - Primary cyan (#00f5ff)
- `color-accent-secondary` - Secondary red (#ff3366)
- `color-accent-success` - Success green (#00ff66)
- `color-accent-gold` - Gold for high scores (#ffd700)

### Text Colors
- `color-text-primary` - White (#ffffff)
- `color-text-secondary` - Muted (#8888aa)
- `color-text-dim` - Disabled (#444466)

### Ghost Piece
- `color-ghost` - Semi-transparent white (15%)
- `color-ghost-border` - Ghost outline (30%)

### Typography
- `font-display` - 'Press Start 2P' for headings/game text
- `font-mono` - 'JetBrains Mono' for stats
- `text-xs` through `text-5xl` - Pixel-perfect scale (8px-48px)

### Game Grid
- `cell-size` - 28px (responsive: 20px mobile, 24px tablet)
- `board-width` - 10 cells
- `board-height` - 20 cells

### Spacing
- `spacing-1` through `spacing-16` - 4px to 64px scale

### Effects
- `glow-*` - Piece glow effects (per color)
- `shadow-panel` - Panel shadows
- `scanline-opacity` - CRT effect (0.03)

## Implementation Guidelines

### CSS Variables
```css
:root {
  --color-void: #0a0a0f;
  --color-grid-bg: #12121a;
  --cell-size: 28px;
  --piece-i: #00f5ff;
  /* ... etc */
}
```

### Tailwind Config
```js
colors: {
  void: '#0a0a0f',
  piece: {
    i: '#00f5ff',
    o: '#ffd700',
    // ... etc
  }
}
```

## When Building UI

1. Reference tokens from `.specs/design-system/tokens.md`
2. Use token names in ASCII mockups
3. Implement using CSS variables or Tailwind config
4. Maintain the retro arcade aesthetic
5. Apply CRT effects (scanlines, vignette) to outer container

## Key Design Principles

- Dark backgrounds with neon accents
- Pixel-perfect fonts ('Press Start 2P')
- Glow effects on tetrominos
- CRT-inspired visual effects
- High contrast for gameplay clarity
